
### ðŸ“„ Tables

#### `Users`
```sql
user_id | username
--------|---------
1       | Alice
2       | Bob
```

#### `Posts`
```sql
post_id | user_id | content
--------|---------|--------
101     | 1       | "Hello world"
102     | 2       | "SQL is fun"
```

#### `Likes`
```sql
like_id | user_id | post_id
--------|---------|--------
201     | 2       | 101   -- Bob liked Alice's post
202     | 1       | 102   -- Alice liked Bob's post
```

---

### âœ… Simple Query: Show Who Liked What

```sql
SELECT 
    u.username AS liker,
    p.content AS liked_post
FROM 
    Likes l
JOIN Users u ON l.user_id = u.user_id
JOIN Posts p ON l.post_id = p.post_id;
```

---

### ðŸ§ª Output

| liker | liked_post     |
|--------|----------------|
| Bob    | Hello world    |
| Alice  | SQL is fun     |

